headline: RSG Q1 Earnings Call: Margins Expand Amid Top-Line Headwinds, Sustainability and M&A in Focus
summary: Waste management company Republic Services (NYSE:RSG) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025 as sales rose 3.8% year on year to $4.01 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.58 per share was 3.5% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
